cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization of web documents. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves ranking and selecting relevant information from a large collection of documents. Additionally, the use of distributed representations suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on coherence and global view could also make it relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
